narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Beginning Yoruba is an introduction to the language spoken mostly in Nigeria and other parts of Western Africa. Professor Adesola makes the language come alive, and we learn a lot about the cultural and social aspects associated with the language.
I would recommend this to all of the students that I know. It is a great class and I learned a lot about the Yoruban culture which was great to learn about. I really annoyed this class.
I would definitely recommend Yoruba to another student. The language is not well known and people are interested in the unknown. It sounds very interesting and the professor is very friendly.
